# Slice S2 -- Carve out the PR-2b automatic drift detector (defer to 0.8.x)

## Model + effort
Launched as `claude -p --model claude-opus-4-7 --effort high` inside a git worktree
branched from main HEAD **after S1 has landed** (so the harness fix `a601d1c` and the
EU-8 harness are present -- you must update one of S1's harness references; see Task 4).

## Context (why -- read first)
PR-2b shipped TWO things: (1) a manual `doctor recompute-mean` verb + recompute core,
and (2) an AUTOMATIC in-ingest distribution-drift detector that recomputes the mean
mid-ingest. The recall problem that justified the auto-detector was root-caused as a
measurement artifact -- the mean is a non-lever (+1.9pp), and `drift_cos_before=1.0000`
showed the pin was already correct. HITL ruling (2026-05-31): **KEEP the recompute core
+ `doctor recompute-mean` verb; CARVE OUT the automatic drift detector + 200k cap +
`MeanRecomputeDeferred` and DEFER them to 0.8.x** (the benefit -- genuine topic drift --
is unmeasured and the auto-path is permanent hot-commit-path complexity).

Required reading (do not re-derive):
- `dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2bc-decision.md` -- section "2b ... MODIFY (carve out / defer)".
- `dev/design/embedder.md` §0.3 ("Adaptive mean refresh (0.7.2 PR-2b ...)"): you are
  editing this -- drop the automatic-detector paragraph, KEEP the doctor-verb paragraph.
- `dev/design/embedder-decision.md` §3.4 (mirror the §0.3 change).
- `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.2-PR-2b-mean-recompute.md` (original design, for orientation).

## Mandate
Remove the automatic in-ingest drift path; keep the manual recompute capability fully
intact and GREEN. RED-first.

