  3906	/// `vector_default.embedding` BLOBs, writes `mean_vec`, and re-quantizes
  3907	/// EVERY row via the existing [`run_pin_and_requantize_pass`] so no row is
  3908	/// left under a stale centering.
  3909	///
  3910	/// This generalizes the EU-5f open-time recovery pin: it has NO "no mean
  3911	/// pinned yet" guard, so it equally serves the FIRST pin (recovery) and a
  3912	/// REFRESH of an already-pinned mean (PR-2b drift / `doctor recompute-mean`).
  3913	/// The caller owns the transaction boundary, which is what makes a fault
  3914	/// between the `mean_vec` UPDATE and re-quantize completion roll back
  3915	/// wholesale (`dev/design/embedder.md` §0.5 atomicity). It does NOT publish
  3916	/// any event — that is the caller's job, strictly post-durable-commit.
  3917	fn recompute_mean_in_tx(
  3918	    tx: &rusqlite::Transaction<'_>,
  3919	    identity: &EmbedderIdentity,
  3920	) -> Result<MeanRecomputeReport, EngineError> {
  3921	    recompute_mean_in_tx_inner(tx, identity, false)
  3922	}
