   156	**Documented failure mode: topic drift.** A workspace that ingests 256
   157	documents about topic A and then pivots to topic B pins a topic-A-skewed
   158	mean and may underperform on topic B. PR-2a quantified this on the real
   159	corpus (the one-source pinned mean sits ~0.82 cosine to the true corpus
   160	mean and costs -10.9pp recall@10). **As of 0.7.2 PR-2b/PR-2bc this is
   161	mitigated ON DEMAND by `doctor recompute-mean`; an AUTOMATIC in-ingest
   162	refresh is DEFERRED to 0.8.x** (see the 0.8.x stub). The pinned mean is no
   163	longer frozen for the workspace's lifetime, but it is only re-derived when
   164	an operator explicitly asks for it.
   165	
   166	**On-demand mean refresh (0.7.2 PR-2b core, narrowed by PR-2bc S2).** The
   167	threshold-pin remains the initial event, but the pinned mean MAY now be
   168	re-derived after pin via the explicit **`doctor recompute-mean` verb**: it
   169	re-derives the FULL-corpus mean and re-quantizes every row, SYNCHRONOUSLY in
   170	one transaction under `commit_gate`, reusing the §0.5 re-quantize pass. It
   171	is ALWAYS allowed, at any corpus size.
   172	
   173	This verb calls `recompute_mean_in_tx` (a generalization of the EU-5f
   174	recovery pin with its "no mean pinned yet" guard dropped), so there is
   175	exactly one re-derive + re-quantize implementation. The
   176	`MeanVecRecomputed { trigger: Manual }` event publishes strictly AFTER the
   177	recompute transaction is durable.
   178	
   179	**DEFERRED to 0.8.x — automatic in-ingest drift detector.** PR-2b also
   180	shipped an automatic detector (per-commit EWMA recent-mean +
   181	`cos(recent, pinned)` threshold + debounce + a `MeanRecomputeDeferred`
   182	notification above a 200k cap) that recomputed the mean mid-ingest. **PR-2bc
   183	S2 carved it out and deferred it to 0.8.x:** its recall premise was refuted
   184	(the mean is a non-lever, +1.9pp; `drift_cos_before = 1.0000` showed the pin
   185	was already correct), its topic-drift benefit is unmeasured, and it was
   186	permanent hot-commit-path complexity. The carved-out design is parked in
---
   223	### 3.4 Recomputation trigger
   224	
   225	| | |
   226	|---|---|
   227	| **Status** | 🔒 Locked for 0.7.1 (no auto-recomputation); **AMENDED in 0.7.2 PR-2b** (escape hatch taken for the MEAN), then **NARROWED in 0.7.2 PR-2bc S2**: the automatic in-ingest drift detector + 200k cap + `MeanRecomputeDeferred` were BUILT under PR-2b and then **DEFERRED to 0.8.x** after the recall premise was refuted; only the explicit `doctor recompute-mean` verb ships in 0.7.2. The drift threshold/debounce numbers below (ratified by HITL 2026-05-30) describe the DEFERRED auto path, retained for the 0.8.x revival. |
   228	| **Picked (0.7.1 baseline)** | Compute-once-on-first-ingest at `MEAN_VEC_PIN_THRESHOLD = 256` docs (`dev/design/embedder.md` §0.3 step 1); pin atomically at the threshold-crossing commit (§0.3 step 2); all subsequent writes leave `mean_vec` unchanged (§0.3 step 3). |
   229	| **Picked (0.7.2 — PR-2b core, narrowed by PR-2bc S2)** | The pinned mean MAY now be REFRESHED after the initial 256-doc pin via the explicit `fathomdb doctor recompute-mean` verb (always allowed, any corpus size). It runs the re-derive + `run_pin_and_requantize_pass` core SYNCHRONOUSLY in one transaction. The AUTOMATIC in-ingest distribution-drift detector (`cos(recent_mean, pinned_mean) < MEAN_DRIFT_COS_THRESHOLD`, suppressed at/above `MEAN_RECOMPUTE_DYNAMIC_MAX = 200_000` rows with a `MeanRecomputeDeferred` notification) was built in PR-2b but **carved out and DEFERRED to 0.8.x** (PR-2bc S2). Refresh of anything OTHER than the mean (full reindex, per-source means) remains out of scope and deferred. |
   230	| **Why the auto path was deferred (PR-2bc, HITL 2026-05-31)** | Its sole original justification — recall — collapsed: the mean is a non-lever (forcing the full-corpus mean moved real recall only +1.9pp; `drift_cos_before = 1.0000` showed PR-2b had already converged the pin during seeding). The auto path was permanent hot-commit-path complexity (per-commit EWMA + cos check + debounce latch + cap branch + deferred-event plumbing) for an UNMEASURED benefit. The manual verb gives operators the same lever on demand at zero standing cost. See `dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2bc-decision.md` §2b and `dev/plans/prompts/0.8.x-auto-mean-drift-DEFERRED.md`. |
   231	| **Locked by** | `dev/design/embedder.md` §0.3 (EU-2) + EU-5a2/EU-5f apply paths; **0.7.2 PR-2b** engine slice (`Engine::recompute_mean` + `doctor recompute-mean`); **0.7.2 PR-2bc S2** carved out the auto detector. |
   232	| **Owning slice** | 0.7.1 EU-2 (closed); 0.7.2 PR-2b (amendment); 0.7.2 PR-2bc S2 (carve-out/defer). |
   233	
   234	**Drift policy (ratified by HITL 2026-05-30; describes the DEFERRED 0.8.x
   235	auto path, NOT shipped in 0.7.2):**
   236	- `MEAN_DRIFT_COS_THRESHOLD = 0.95`. Calibrated from PR-2a's evidence: a
   237	  pathological topic-skewed pinned mean sits ~0.82 cosine to the true
   238	  corpus mean (the EU-7 -10.9pp recall failure); a representative/healthy
   239	  mean ~0.998. 0.95 sits inside that gap, biased toward the healthy end so
   240	  the detector fires on genuine sustained drift, not benign jitter.
   241	- `MEAN_RECOMPUTE_DEBOUNCE_ROWS = 256` + falling-edge re-arm latch: after
   242	  one recompute (or deferred notification) the detector will not fire again
   243	  until ≥256 further rows commit AND it has re-armed (cos recovered above
   244	  threshold). One drift episode therefore triggers at most one recompute.
   245	- Recent-mean estimator: an EWMA with `alpha = 1/256` (O(dim) memory,
   246	  O(dim)/row, no history buffer) — chosen over a hard sliding window which
   247	  would need a W·dim ring buffer for the same responsiveness.
   248	
   249	**Why SYNCHRONOUS in-transaction (and not the originally-rejected
   250	background worker):** PR-2b reuses the EU-5f at-pin re-quantize machinery
   251	verbatim, which is already transactional and serialized under `commit_gate`.
   252	Doing the refresh in the same tx inherits that crash-atomicity for free (a
   253	fault between the `mean_vec` UPDATE and the re-quantize rolls back wholesale
   254	— no half-recentered corpus) and needs NO new background-worker
   255	infrastructure, which was the specific reason auto-recomputation was
   256	rejected for 0.7.1. The cost is bounded by the `MEAN_RECOMPUTE_DYNAMIC_MAX`
   257	cap on the automatic path; the unbounded case (the doctor verb at very large
   258	N) is an explicit operator action.
   259	
   260	**Considered but rejected (0.7.1 — re-examined for PR-2b):**
   261	- **> 25% row-count delta heuristic** — still rejected as the *trigger*:
   262	  row-count delta is a proxy; the real signal is distribution shift. PR-2b
   263	  triggers on the distribution signal DIRECTLY (cosine drift of a running
   264	  recent-vector mean against the pinned mean), which is what that heuristic
   265	  was a stand-in for. The "no background-worker infra" objection is mooted
   266	  by the synchronous-in-tx choice above.
   267	- **Recompute on every `Engine.open`** — still rejected; O(N) startup cost
   268	  and a moving target for the sign-bit cache. PR-2b recomputes only on a
   269	  detected drift edge or an explicit verb, never unconditionally at open.
   270	  (The EU-5f open-time *recovery* pin — only when a mean is unexpectedly
   271	  NULL above threshold — is unchanged and remains the only open-time path.)
   272	- **Per-source-type mean** — still rejected and explicitly NOT covered by
   273	  PR-2b; corpus-wide mean only.
   274	
   275	**Known limitation carried forward (now mitigated on demand, not closed):**
   276	topic-drift workspaces pin a skewed mean and may underperform until an
   277	operator runs `doctor recompute-mean`. As of 0.7.2 (PR-2bc S2) refresh is
   278	ENTIRELY operator-driven — the automatic in-ingest detector and its
   279	`MeanRecomputeDeferred`/200k-cap surfaces were deferred to 0.8.x. Full
   280	reindex and per-source means remain deferred.

