### 1. [medium] Closure artifact records the wrong slice head
Refs: [0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-output.json](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-output.json:4)

The checked-out branch head is `1492f461999e1e18953cefd48ddfbd363ee59d16`, but the required closure artifact records `"head_sha": "639d04c ..."`. `639d04c` exists, but it is not the actual current head for this slice.  
That does not change the code result, but it makes the required bookkeeping artifact inaccurate.

### 2. [low] One engine API comment still describes a removed deferred event
Refs: [lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2333)

`Engine::drain_embedder_events()` still says it drains “mean pin, mean recompute, deferred-recompute notification”. The deferred notification surface was removed with `MeanRecomputeDeferred`.  
This is only a stale comment, not live behavior, but the slice mandate was “no dead code left behind” and repo policy explicitly treats stale comments as harmful.

**What passed on inspection**

- The automatic path is gone from live engine code: `ProjectionRuntimeShared` no longer carries `recent_mean` / `mean_recompute_dynamic_max`, `commit_projection_outcomes` no longer contains the drift block, and the remaining path only does initial pinning plus manual recompute via [`lib.rs`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3718).
- The manual path remains intact and uses the shared core: [`Engine::recompute_mean`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2364) still serializes on `commit_gate`, calls `recompute_mean_in_tx_inner`, commits before publishing [`MeanVecRecomputed { trigger: Manual }`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2394), and the core still reuses [`run_pin_and_requantize_pass`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3974). Initial pin-at-256 logic is unchanged in [`commit_projection_outcomes`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3754).
- The RED guard is genuine, not tautological: [`topic_pivot_does_not_auto_recompute_mid_ingest`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/pr2b_mean_recompute.rs:202) pins an A-skewed mean, floods B past the old debounce window, asserts no recompute event, and asserts the pinned bytes stay unchanged. In the parent version of the test file, the three removed tests were exactly the auto-path tests: `drift_recompute_improves_topic_b_recall`, `homogeneous_corpus_does_not_recompute`, and `cap_suppresses_auto_but_not_manual`.
- The py/CLI/napi ripple is functionally complete: only `MeanVecRecomputed` is serialized in [`CLI`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/lib.rs:501), [`py`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:444), and [`napi`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs:450). `MeanRecomputeTrigger` now only exposes `Manual` in [`embedder`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder/src/lib.rs:51).
- The docs honestly describe the deferral and keep N=256 locked: [`embedder.md §0.3`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/dev/design/embedder.md:156), [`embedder-decision.md §3.4`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/dev/design/embedder-decision.md:223), and the parked [`0.8.x stub`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/dev/plans/prompts/0.8.x-auto-mean-drift-DEFERRED.md:1) are aligned.
- S1’s search-limit seam was not disturbed: the harness still uses [`set_search_limit_for_test`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:444), and the manual-only [`EU7_FORCE_FULL_RECOMPUTE`](/tmp/fdb-0.7.2-PR-2bc-S2-20260531T131418Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:741) path remains.

**Reviewer process notes**

- Review was read-only and based on the required docs, commit history `62c161e..1492f46`, targeted diffs, and symbol sweeps across `src/` and relevant `dev/` docs.
- I did not rerun the test suite in this pass. The pre-existing `ac_007b_slow_threshold_reconfigurable` flake was treated as out of scope, as requested.
